Production Company: CTORA Productions

Rehearsal Schedule

April 8 ‚Äì April 30, 2026

Wed‚ÄìFri: 10:00 a.m. ‚Äì 6:00 p.m.

Sat‚ÄìSun: 12:00 p.m. ‚Äì 8:00 p.m.

Tech Week: May 1 ‚Äì May 7

Performances: May 8 ‚Äì 17 (10 shows)

Granville Island Stage Theatre

Creative Team

Director: Sarah Rodgers

Music Director: Jeremy Hoffman

Choreographer: Ken Overbey

Self-Tape Submissions Now Open!

Please submit the following materials to auditions@ctora.ca by November 10, 2025:

 1. Headshot

 2. R√©sum√©

 3. Dance reel

 4. Singing reel

 5. Cover letter

Find detailed instructions on CTORA‚Äôs General Auditions page https://ctora.ca/about#jobs-auditions

CTORA welcomes performers 18+ of all genders, ethnicities, and abilities to audition, seeing Equity performers for select roles under the DOT Agreement and Non-Equity performers with an honorarium.

Deadline to Apply: November 10, 2025

Selected candidates will be invited to in-person  auditions on Nov 29, 30, and Dec 1, with callbacks on Dec 5, 6, and 8.

DANNY ZUKO: Male, High School Teen (Range: tenor, D4‚ÄìB5)The leader of the Burger Palace Boys; good-looking, strong and confident, with an air of easy-going charm.

SANDY DUMBROWSKI: Female, High School Teen (Range: Soprano, A3‚ÄìF#5) New girl in town; sweet, wholesome, naive, cute, and innocent.

BETTY RIZZO: Female, High School Teen (Range:Alto A3‚ÄìC5)Leader of the Pink Ladies; tough, sarcastic, and outspoken but vulnerable.

FRENCHY: Female, High School Teen (Range: Alto, A3‚ÄìD5)A dreamer; good-natured but not too smart, she is heavily made up, fussy about her appearance, particularly her hair. She can't wait to finish high school so she can be a beautician.

MARTY: Female, High School Teen (Range Alto, C4‚ÄìC5)The 'beauty' of the Pink Ladies; pretty and looks older than the other girls, but betrays her real age when she opens her mouth. She tries to act sophisticated.

JAN: Female, High School Teen (Range: Alto, A3-C5)

Funny, loud, compulsive eater, and awkward member of the Pink Ladies. Loud and pushy with the girls, but shy with boys.

DOODY: Male, High School Teen (Range: Tenor, D4-A5)The youngest of the guys; small, boyish, and open, with a disarming smile and a hero-worshipping attitude towards the other guys. He also plays the guitar.

KENICKIE: Male, High School Teen (Range: Tenor, C4‚ÄìF5)The second in command of the Burger Palace Boys; tough-looking, tattooed, surly, and avoids any show of softness. He has an offbeat sense of humor.

SONNY LATIERRI: Male, High School Teen (Range: baritone, G3‚ÄìA5)A member of the Burger Palace Boys; funny Italian-American, he is a braggart and wheeler-dealer who thinks he's a real lady-killer

ROGER: Male, High School Teen (Range: Tenor, D4-A5)

The anything-for-a-laugh stocky type of boy; a clown who enjoys winding people up, he is full of mischief and is always dreaming up half-baked schemes and ideas.

VINCE FONTAINE: Male, High School Teen (Range: Ensemble/Part Flexible)A typical 'teen audience' disc jockey; slick, egotistical and fast-talking. He is also a veteran 'Greaser.'

CHA-CHA, aka CHARLENE, DIGREGORIO: Female, High School Teen (Range: Alto, C4‚ÄìC5) The best dancer at St. Bernadette's; a loud mouth, she wins the dancing competition with Danny.

EUGENE FLORCZYK: Male, High School Teen (Range: Tenor, A3‚ÄìE5)The class valedictorian; physically awkward, with weak eyes and a high-pitched voice. He's a typical 'apple-polisher' - both smug and pompous, but gullible.

JOHNNY CASINO: Male, High School Teen (Range: Tenor, G4-E5)All-American, rock-star ‚Äúgreaser‚Äù student at Rydell High, whose real name is Clarence.

MISS LYNCH: Female, Age Flexible (Range: Ensemble/Part Flexible)A no-nonsense, serious, loud English teacher.

PATTY SIMCOX: Female, High School Teen (Range: Alto, D4-A4) A typical cheerleader; attractive, athletic, sure-of-herself, but can be given to bursts of disconcerting enthusiasm. She's a bit of a pain and unpopular with the Pink Ladies, and can twirl a baton.

TEEN ANGEL: Male, Age Flexible (Range: Tenor, E4‚ÄìF5)Frenchy's suave and slick guardian angel, who encourages her to stay in school. 

THE PINK LADIES: Ensemble (SATB) The club-jacketed, gum-chewing, hip-swinging girls' gang who hang around with the Burger Palace Boys.

THE BURGER PALACE BOYS: Ensemble (SATB)

A super-cool, DA-haired, hard-looking group of high school wheeler-dealers... or so they think.

Radio Voice: Male, Age Flexible (Rage: Tenor, A3‚ÄìC5)

A Radio Voice

items.text:
Hello, 
We are looking for two performers to act in a short movie. ‚ÄúWhere the Light Shines‚Äù explores denial, anxiety, and female identity in a male-dominated society. The film reflects the tension between masculine and feminine energy ‚Äì control and surrender ‚Äì and how these forces collide in the face of inner truth.
The story uses contemporary movement and dance to showcase the troubled inner-word of the characters. You will be working closely with the director and choreographer to shape the narrative.
Females, non-binary and all ethnicities is encouraged to apply!<3 This is a third year Bachelor project.  
If you are ready to move with the lights, contact us at: edsh.production@gmail.com.

items.text:
Hello fellow Colorado actors. Many of you may not know that as a SAG member actors need to follow SAG rules. I have seen several violations of SAG rules, not only in our Denver market, but in New Mexico as well. Did you know that SAG rule 14 states:

A member cannot work as both a performer and a casting director, or a performer and a member of another theatrical teamster union, on the same production without the union's consent? 

Actors should not be casting directors due to a conflict of interest, as it can lead to biased decision-making in favor of their own acting career, and because the two roles require different skill sets. 

A casting director's job is to serve the production's needs by finding the best fit for a role, a process that requires a separate and objective perspective from the actor's self-interest in getting cast. 

If you know of anyone that is breaking SAG rule 14, I urge you to call or email SAG in Los Angeles and ask to speak with their violation‚Äôs department. You can also make the claim anonymously!Ôøº

SAG-AFTRA / (855) 724-2387
info@sagaftra.org

Meanwhile most productions are nonunion in Colorado with WAY bigger fish to fry‚Ä¶

HOLDING PATTERN: A film noir by Nico Guin from Denver School of the Arts‚Äô VCA department!
Looking for 3 actors for a 5-minute film-noir!When a wealthy business woman meets a new love interest, she puts him to the test through a private investigator to find out if he can be trusted. 
Roles are not paid or promised.

ESTELLE - The younger wealthy business woman who is in love with John. She wants to test his potential as a love interest, but things take a turn. Estelle is cold, harsh, and confident, while also being sympathetic and unsettling.
JOHN -  John, a younger man who spends whatever money he has at the bar, who has been dating Estelle for a few months and really likes her. Unfortunately, when presented by Victor with the option to steal her fortune in the form of stocks and bonds, he decides the money is too enticing to decline, leading to his ultimate demise. 
VICTOR - The mysterious private investigator hired by Estelle to test whether or not John can be trusted as her future partner. He is ambiguous yet seemingly trustworthy to John, and offers him the job to steal Estelle‚Äôs assets.

We will be shooting during the first 3 weekends of November, and are pretty flexible with time of day! 
If you are interested or have any questions, you can reach out to me at 914900@dpsk12.net or 720-255-2717. Thank you!

items.text:
In my mid-twenties I was working enough as an actress to have health insurance paid for through SAG. I was over the moon! I thought, things can only get better from here - I'm a 'real' actor and on my way. Little did I know, life had other plans for me. A year later, I fell in love with a German man and moved to Germany to start a new chapter in my life; "Family."

Everything was new - the language, the culture, being a wife and mother, and not having access to my creative community and opportunities... My identity has always been very wrapped up in being an actor but how was that supposed to work now? Here?

It took a while to adjust, but within a couple of years I found my footing doing voiceover, commercials and presenting. Things were good on the career front. Not great but good - Money was coming in, I had lot's of flexibility, I could take my son and my dog to the studio with me and still be home in time to get dinner ready. (Yes, we had a very traditional marriage).

But this wasn't how I had pictured my work life when I dreamed of an acting career. I wanted more. I wanted to sink my teeth into meaty roles and make a difference in people's lives through my art. On the other hand, I felt so ungrateful. I had a beautiful family and was "technically" earning my living as an actor but I wasn't fulfilled.

So when my son grew up, I finally had a little time to think about what I wanted and the answer was startling. I still wanted my acting career.

But now, I was 47 and still living in Germany. I had no current showreel material, no industry contacts and didn't know how I was going to make sense of the 16 year gap in my career. I very quickly realized that my success as a younger actress wasn't down to any particular knowledge or strategy. I just got lucky. This time, I was going to have to figure something else out.

But even that was nothing compared to what felt like the biggest hurdle of all ‚Äì I was super rusty. I hadn't done any real acting in almost 2 decades, and my instrument was extremely out of tune. It seemed like the problem was also revealing the solution: I needed training to get my skills and confidence back to where I felt ready to tackle getting back out there professionally. But living in Munich, and finding good, affordable training in English seemed even more impossible.

The way I saw it, I had two options: I could fly to L.A., N.Y., or London and get the training I needed (which would have been extremely expensive and time-consuming), or I could give up. Giving up wasn't an option.

Since my problem was so specific ‚Äì needing affordable, high-level acting training in English, right here in Munich ‚Äì it clicked that I'd have to figure out the solution myself. So, I decided to try organizing the workshops I needed.

What happened next changed everything I thought I knew about following your passions.
I got the training I needed ‚Äì and because I was the organizer, I always got that training for free. A real community started to form around the workshops too, which was fantastic. Unexpectedly, it also turned into a way to bring in steady money, which honestly made a big difference on so many different levels.

But the biggest discovery was this: I didn't need to be the expert to create something valuable around what I was passionate about. I just needed to be curious enough to bring the right people together.

Flash forward almost 15 years of using this approach myself. As I started sharing what I'd learned, I kept hearing the same thing: people with genuine interests ‚Äì fermentation, vintage furniture restoration, urban beekeeping, traditional crafts ‚Äì immediately dismissing them as "not realistic" for making money. They believed you either needed to be an ‚Äúexpert‚Äù or resign yourself to keeping passions as expensive hobbies.

But I knew that wasn't true. The same thing that worked for my acting workshops could work for any genuine interest.

I'm not saying any of this to brag - though I am proud of what I've learned. I'm saying this so whoever reads it will know that you, too, can turn what you love into what supports you.

If you have genuine interests you've dismissed as "not realistic" for creating income, here are three things you can think about right now:
‚û°Ô∏è Your specific learning needs are actually market research - if you want it, others do too.
‚û°Ô∏è You don't need to be the expert - you need to be the person who brings experts and learners together.
‚û°Ô∏è If you're waiting to be "qualified enough," you're missing the point entirely.

Sometimes creating what you wish existed is the most direct path to living the life you actually want. You have the power inside of you to organize the experiences you're craving, no matter what stage of life you're in, as long as you're brave enough to take it.

Been cooking up a lot of projects behind the scenes and this is the most recent! 

Currently casting for a new short, working title 'The Heist', filming in Northern Quarter, Manchester!

In 1994, a duo of thieves, interrogated after a heist gone wrong, find their fates decided by the value of their mysterious stolen item ü™ô

STUDENT FILM, SHOOTING IN MANCHESTER, EARLY NOV, UNPAID

THE INTERROGATOR

mid 30s. 

Stoic but becomes fascinated with the two thieves' stories. 

RAY

20 - 30

Confident, in charge and narcissistic. Takes the lead within the duo

NICK

18 - 25

new to the crime world, scruffy and erratic. Intimidated by Ray.

Within plenty of space to collaborate, build and bring your own energy and flair to the story and the characters, this may be a good opportunity for upcoming actors building their portfolio and looking for experience! 

We are currently looking for self tape auditions

If interested please message me here or email izzyhambury1@gmail.com

for further details

# Casting Call 

**ARTHUR: **Male-identifying, late 30s-early 40s. Uptight. 

**SYNOPSIS**

In the dead of night and the middle of winter, a slapdash team chop firewood - but nature has other plans for them‚Ä¶

From the writer of ‚ÄòMemory‚Äôs Recess‚Äô (CGTC, 2023) Ben Chesler, *Drop Dead* is an Australian Gothic play that‚Äôll make you think twice about venturing out into the bush at night.

**More information**

This is an unpaid role in a one-act play, apart of festival being produced by CGTC. Rehearsing on Wednesday evenings with performances in early March. 

Auditions on the evening of 03/11 in Melbourne.

If you're interested, DM me

items.text:
**Casting call

English Micro Drama ‰∏®Filming in Qingdao, China‰∏®Nov 25 to Dec 5, 2025

 

Genre: modern, hidden identity

Compensation: paid

Shooting period: 7 to 9 days

 

Characters

*Richard (Lead, Male, 38yrs, White): A devoted househusband / a powerful CEO

 

*Olivia (Lead, Female, 33yrs, White): A beautiful and capable woman with a sharp, professional demeanor.

 

*Scott (Main supporting role, Male, 36yrs, White): Appears to be gentle and gracious, but is in fact hypocritical and selfish.

 

*Lydia (Main supporting role, Female, 33yrs, White): An elite woman with charisma and authority, never meek or compliant.

 

*Emma (Main supporting role, Female, 15yrs, White): A rebellious teenager, impulsive, spoiled, and cares too much about appearances.

 

*Travis (Main supporting role, Male, 14yrs, White): A rebellious teenager, spoiled and vain

 

*Denise (Main supporting role, Female, 30yrs): an assistant, gentle, kind, and perceptive

 

We prefer actors currently based in Mainland China, but we‚Äôre open to discussing with exceptional talents from other regions.

 

Please DM with a resume, a headshot shot and reels (if applicable)

If you‚Äôre looking international , top level training . Spotlight approved and SAG recognised then give us a message as we offer in person , online and one to one coaching. 

Why settle for generic text book coaching, why settle for one method fits all . Why settle going to a class week in and week out and never actually gaining anything for your cv or your showreel.

sharedPost.text:
Another happy actor ‚Ä¶. A great review from Mereli 

I recently had a one to one coaching class with Chris in preparation for an upcoming audition
I expected advice but got so much more. He himself is a fantastic Actor had taken the audition piece.  He broke down the character so i could clearly understand the person i would be playing. It made me realise how many off my own character traits existed in the role. This made it so much easier.  I have never had an acting lesson so informative and helpful before. This man really cares, takes his time, explains things clearly and explained why there is certain things i need to do to  do this "Woman" justice
If you are looking for coaching from a Actor with many amazing productions under his belt but still cares about the students journey  Foundry Acting Studio is worth serious consideration.  Affordable and fantastic

The best coaching i have ever had. Chris had the piece i needed to work on for my audition for a couple of hours and had worked on the characters personality traits, emotional objective, love language, sub text and the beats of entire piece. He gave me such a deeper understanding of her and the confidence to see how  my own personality traits were in some ways so similiar
I havent done the audition yet but know when i do im going to be so much better prepared than i was before working with Chris
Thank you Chris and Claire. 
This man is the real deal. He cares about the Actors he is working with and explains things making them understandable. It is the first of many coaching sessions i hope to have with him
I came into the industry at age 60 so didnt have great confidence in myself and this man has made me believe i can do so much more

If you‚Äôre looking in person , one to one or online classes . Message us today.

sharedPost.text:
üåÄüåÄüé•üèÜHighly advanced acting course on.line

---

üé¨ Unlock the Mind, Unlock the Scene

Ever wondered why some performances hit you right in the gut, while others just float by? It‚Äôs not luck ‚Äî it‚Äôs psychology, philosophy, and instinct.

In my course, we go deep into the human mind:

Freud ‚Üí Understand the hidden drives, inner conflicts, and desires that shape your character.

Jung ‚Üí Explore archetypes, shadows, and the collective patterns that give your role mythic resonance.

Nietzsche ‚Üí Learn to embrace struggle, chaos, and life itself, transforming it into raw energy for your performance.

This isn‚Äôt abstract theory ‚Äî it‚Äôs practical, on-set knowledge:

Build characters that feel alive, complex, and unforgettable.

Hit the emotional beats instinctively.

Turn tension, darkness, and chaos into performance gold.

Whether you‚Äôre in front of the camera or behind it, these tools take your craft to another level.

üí• Your mind is your stage ‚Äî let‚Äôs train it to perform.
LONG VERSION üåÄ1 to 1 on ZOOM,intensive,acting workshop.helping to push your emotions to the edge.leading to a powerful "sizzle"reel and possible employment on the 8 features I am shooting this year and next..long version.

Including "river talks"produced by "little pig films"

üåÄüé¨üé•üåö Exclusive 1-on-1 Acting Workshop

üî• Limited-Time Offer ‚Äì Only a Few Spots Left! üî•
(üì© Message Now to Secure Yours!)

"Imagine walking into an audition with unshakable confidence, delivering a performance so raw and real that the director can't look away."

This isn‚Äôt just another acting class. It‚Äôs an intensive experience designed to break barriers and elevate your craft.

---

üé≠ What Makes This Course Different?

"This course integrates the poetic realism of Tarkovsky, the practical wisdom of Michael Caine, and the transformative techniques of Stanislavski and Method Acting. Designed to deepen your craft, it focuses on authentic emotional connection and powerful storytelling."

Along with working with, Freud, Yung,and Nietzsche..to understand "subtext and archetypes".

üé¨ Created by a British Cinematographer/Director with 31 Years of Experience and 32 Features to His Name

üåç International Experience: Having worked on films worldwide, collaborating with actors and directors, I bring real-world insights from both sides of the camera. This course is designed to give actors a deep understanding of their craft, emphasizing emotional depth and character development.

üìΩ IMDb: www.imdb.com/name/nm1806508

üìΩ Showreel: https://enkiproductions1.8b.io

---

üé¨ Exclusive Opportunity ‚Äì A Direct Path to Real Work!

At the end of the course, each student will create a high-impact ‚Äúsizzle reel‚Äù, showcasing their strongest performance moments.

üîπ This reel will be personally passed on to the directors of the next 7 feature films I am working on as cinematographer.

üîπ That means real exposure‚Äîreal opportunities‚Äîreal chances for work.

üé≠ "This isn‚Äôt just training. This is your shot to be seen by directors actively casting for upcoming projects."

---

ü§î What You Will Learn:

üåÄ Emotional Range ‚Äì Master a full spectrum of emotions for believable, compelling performances.

üåÄ Character Development ‚Äì Create rich, multidimensional characters with depth and 
realism.

üåÄ Method Acting ‚Äì Use personal experiences to deliver raw, authentic performances.

üåÄ Working with Directors & Crew ‚Äì Learn how to hit marks, understand shooting ratios, and collaborate effectively.

üåÄ Scene Preparation ‚Äì Techniques for script interpretation, emotional connection, and performing under pressure.

üåÄ Industry Standards ‚Äì Create a professional showreel and understand how to stand out to casting directors.

---

üé¨ These Courses Are One-on-One with the Mentor/Director, Who Will Push You to Make the Performance Believable.

---

üé¨ Course Breakdown

Day 1: Moment-to-Moment Acting (Stanislavski‚Äôs Approach)

üîπ Breaking a Scene Down: Internal visualization and meditation to "become" the character.

üîπ Character Exercise: The Hitman‚Äôs First Kill

üìç Scene: A low-rent hotel room in Manhattan, lit by a dull winter‚Äôs midday light. The sad hum of a ceiling fan, distant sirens, muted traffic below. On the bed‚Äîa brand-new sniper rifle.(You will be encouraged to "visualize"this)

üí• "Actors I've trained have gone on to land real roles‚Äîthis course gives you what drama schools miss."

üîπ Exercise 1: Enter the room, pick up the gun, examine it, and prepare for the target.

üîπ Exercise 2: Explore multiple emotional shifts (relief, doubt, fascination, decision).

üåÄYou have entered the room you are safe (singular emotion)

üåÄYou see the gun on the bed,the awareness of your reality sinks in.

üåÄYou make a descion to approach the gun 

üåÄYou pick up the gun,initially you are captivated by the mastery of it,s creation (momentarily distracting you from the reality of what you are about to do.)

üåÄYou make the descion to kill(remember in this excercise this is a 1st time "hit person"..why do you make that descion?(Covered in class).

üåÄYou move to the window,practical ,Now you have decided action will take place.

Explore why using stanislavski techniques,of breaking a scene into ,moment by moment.

It is more fascinating to watch.on screen,the audience does not know "what is going on in your head"..but it is fascinated to watch,and it captures your audience.

üîπ Discussion: How do actors like Heath Ledger, Daniel Day-Lewis, and Dustin Hoffman make their characters so real? Insights from my own experiences on set.

üåÄ:(monologue)an actor,s ability to memorize lines is important .

üé¨:in the style of "the late great heath ledger of "Batman dark knights"(a crazed man sits with a portable nuclear bomb,on his lap):

üåÄ"So you imagine chaos was created in a day?(Sinister,sarcastic)(Pause/breath)"do you think e equals m squared (slow word by word,as if talking to a child),means we can travel back in time?(Smiles,and cricks his/her neck),no it just means we can build an atom bomb!!,and blow things up!(Smiles and claps hands gleefully),we are all going to die (bows as if on stage),and just by chance we,ll remember why.(Pause)...we even did this?,looks at camera slowly . reflectivity,or just perhaps...mmm I don,t know "nobody cares"!!!!!!.

Lifts button to camera and presses it!!!!..

Boom!!!(Note my last student took the entire session to make this believable).

End scene.üé¨üé¨

---

Day 2: Making Your Character Believable

üîπ Understanding the Psyche: Whether playing a killer or an ordinary person, you must know your character‚Äôs mind.research I had a director friend who contacted "Liam neelson"to understand him
Heath ledger locked himself in a hotel room
The actor from the "machinenist"almost starved himself to death.

üîπ Character Exercise: The Breaking Point

üìç Scene: A crowded supermarket. A tired voice announces deals over the PA. You feel unseen, unheard, frustrated‚Äîuntil suddenly, you‚Äôre holding an AK-47. (Scenes can be altered if a student is uncomfortable.)you open fire!!!.

Bang bang bang.
The feeling of power and saying 
F......you all.

Is almost zen like just firing the gun,every round as it falls to the ground is an expression of the rage of anger you feel about ,been born, having to survive,having to make a living,for this day and this day only!(You know for sure the police will kill you)

But this is your day!!!

I will direct you for this scene.

To make it believable

You will have to use "method"and the ability to "source"that"inner rage(which we all have).
To make the scene believable.

Shown to directors I know ..I imagine (if done right,they will be "blown away")

üîπ Alternative Scene: A Joker-like monologue before detonation.

I have script from this scene we can work with.
But it explores "chaos/anarchist"concepts (as expressed by the joker (heath ledger )In "Batman dark knights"

üîπ Alternative Scene: A video call to the person you love most‚Äîdesperately trying to convince them not to leave.

The point of this scene (if you choose it)is to make your performance totally believable.

üé≠ "Imagine the tension of a final phone call‚Äîthe stakes couldn‚Äôt be higher. This is where real acting happens."

üîπ Accents: British, American (Deep South), and Northern Irish accents for performance versatility.

üîπ Final Exercise: The Power of Stillness ‚Äì convey pure serenity in front of the camera.

The American Indians used to say "a camera steal,s your soul"

A film camera can almost "see inside you"
The purpose of this course is to help you create that "believability"and emotion.

---

Day 3: Working with a Director and Crew

üîπ Understanding your role in the filmmaking process.

üîπ Technical skills: hitting marks, lighting awareness, and camera shooting ratios.
If you don,t appreciate what your crew does,and are say arrogant,well does not make for a nice shoot?

Most actor,s I have worked with are empathetic,kind and understanding 
üîπ Collaborating with crew‚Äîcontinuity, sound, makeup, cinematography, and direction.

üìΩ Final Showreel Scenes:

üé≠ Sinister: "So you really think you got away with it?" You imagine that your karma was not noted,your actions had no consequences.

üé≠ Heartbroken: "But I didn‚Äôt mean it... please, don‚Äôt leave me‚Ä¶I know now that without you I could never imagine how my life would be"

üé≠ Insane (Joker-like): "Mmm... if E = mc¬≤, then time versus chaos... Means excistance is just a theory ,I have this bomb..the one thing Einstein /Oppenheimer manager to create..so bye bye..let,s push the button!!

üé≠ Flat & Emotionless: "We‚Äôre born, we live, we die. That‚Äôs it." If heaven exists,and we are re.born with "conciseness ",then heaven would become like hell,
As "time"and a sense of time ,knowing we are going one day ,gives us ..in way (deep pause look to camera)a security.

---

Day 4: Fear and Survival ‚Äì Personal Experience & Character Creation

üîπ Deep Dive: Exploring fear, survival, and desperation in character work.

üîπ Exercise 1: The Jungle Escape
üìç Scene: You‚Äôre lost in the jungle at night. Every step is agony, but stopping means death. You call out‚Äîpleading for help. No answer.

üé≠ Emotions to Explore:

1. Fear of death ‚Äì the realization that no one is coming.

2. Desperation ‚Äì the raw instinct to survive.

3. Physical exhaustion ‚Äì feeling your body give in.

üîπ Exercise 2: The Final Phone Call Redux
üìç Scene: You‚Äôre on the phone with a loved one. You need their help. If they refuse, it‚Äôs over.

üé≠ "This isn‚Äôt just acting‚Äîit‚Äôs about reaching deep into your own experiences to find truth in the performance."

------

üé¨:Session 5: Unlocking the Inner World ‚Äî Freud, Jung, and Nietzsche in Action

 üö®A short script will be given:

üé•:."Sometimes I just can,t feel my self inside,it,s as if something is missing ,but ..I can,t quite put my finger on it"

Jung ,Freud and Nietzsche will be discussed in class...there different philosophies on life .

Perform the script 3 times with those different subtexts in mind.

---

Objective:

To integrate the psychological and philosophical concepts we've explored (Freud's hidden desires, Jung's archetypes, and Nietzsche's self-empowerment) into a character's internal journey, enhancing the depth of performance and pushing actors toward more complex, dynamic roles.

---

üö®1. Understanding the Inner Conflict (Freud)

Exercise:
Guide your actors to explore a hidden desire or repressed emotion within their character that contradicts their outward behavior.
Example: An actor playing a ‚Äústoic‚Äù hero could uncover a deep fear of abandonment they are trying to repress, which sneaks through in moments of weakness.(Script will be given)

üåÄGoal:
Reveal the complexity of a character by exploring subconscious drives and how they create inner conflict in their actions.

---

üö®2. Finding the Archetypes (Jung)

üåÄExercise:
Ask your actors to identify which archetype (Hero, Shadow, Wise Old Man, Rebel, etc.) their character is embodying in the scene.
Then, have them break the archetype ‚Äî let them experiment with how the character could act outside their usual role to reveal something deeper about their personal growth.(Script will be given)

üåÄGoal:
Explore how different archetypes influence a character‚Äôs actions and how those archetypes evolve through the story.

---

üö®3. Creating the √úbermensch Moment (Nietzsche)

üåÄExercise:
Have your actors play out a moment where their character faces a crucible‚Äîa choice that pushes them beyond their old self and forces them to create their own values.
Example: A character might choose self-sacrifice to uphold their personal code, even though it risks everything (script will be given)

Goal:
Challenge the actor to play moments of personal transformation, where their character is creating their own power in the face of destruction or moral ambiguity.

---

üåÄ4. Integration and Performance

Exercise:
Give your actors a scene where all three elements come into play:

Freud's inner conflict (hidden desires or repressions)

Jung's archetypes (the character wearing multiple masks)

Nietzsche‚Äôs self-empowerment (the character breaking free and reimagining their world)
Guide them to play the scene with all these layers, digging into the internal battle, archetypal masks, and the potential for self-transformation.(Script will be given).

Goal:
Combine these psychological and philosophical elements to create a rich, multi-dimensional character.

---

Wrap-Up:

Discuss how each character‚Äôs internal journey was shaped by their hidden emotions, their spiritual archetypes, and their search for power.

Reflect on how they can continue to explore their characters‚Äô deeper layers in future roles.

üé¨ Final Performance (Day 4):

Students will perform a final emotional scene, bringing together everything they‚Äôve learned. These performances will be recorded as raw material for their showreel.

üí• Their best moments will be compiled into a high-impact sizzle reel‚Äîdirectly sent to directors casting for upcoming feature films.
That I am either producing or about to be cinematographer on.

---

üé¨üé• Ready to Elevate Your Acting?

üî• For Less Than the Price of a Casting Workshop, You Get 1-on-1 Coaching and a Real Chance for Work!

üì¢ LIMITED SPOTS AVAILABLE ‚Äì MESSAGE NOW TO SECURE YOUR PLACE!

üì© DM or Email: mikeenkiproductions1@gmail.com

Let‚Äôs create something unforgettable.
---

---

Mike Muschamp‚Äôs Philosophy Map ‚Äì The Big Five

1Ô∏è‚É£ Freud ‚Äì The Mind‚Äôs Hidden Drives

Core idea: Unconscious desires and fears shape behavior.

Use in acting/storytelling: Know why characters (and people) do what they do. Subtle gestures, hesitation, tension = meaningful.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Jung ‚Äì Archetypes & Shadows

Core idea: Universal patterns, archetypes, and the hidden ‚Äúshadow‚Äù influence life.

Use in acting/storytelling: Tap into archetypes to make characters mythic; explore shadow for emotional depth.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Nietzsche ‚Äì Will to Power & Self-Overcoming

Core idea: Life is chaos; create your own meaning and values.

Use in acting/storytelling: Turn struggle into strength, show transformation, act boldly.

4Ô∏è‚É£ Camus ‚Äì Absurdity & Joy in Struggle

Core idea: Life has no inherent meaning; joy comes from living fully despite it.

Use in acting/storytelling: Embrace absurdity in scenes, add existential tension and truth.

5Ô∏è‚É£ Viktor Frankl (‚ÄúFrank‚Äù) ‚Äì Meaning in Suffering

Core idea: Even in suffering, humans can find purpose; choosing your attitude = freedom.

Use in acting/storytelling: Transform hardship into performance, purpose, and inspiration.

---

How They Mix Together ‚Äì Your Signature Lens

Freud + Jung: Understand inner drives and archetypal patterns.

Nietzsche + Camus: Embrace chaos, self-overcome, find joy in struggle.

Frank: Give all of it purpose; turn learning and life into meaning.

Result: A philosophical toolkit that powers acting, directing, writing, and living

**CASTING CALL for indie feature film                                                      (Non Union/Volunteer/Unpaid/IMDB credits)**

**Synopsis:**

**A couple migrate to Canada from a small town in India in search of a better life, but what makes them quit half way and go back to their country even when people around them are flourishing. Is it the system that is broken or there‚Äôs a dent in the mindset itself?**

**Character description:**

**Rude Female Customer**
** *****Age:***** 40‚Äì55**
** *****Ethnicity:***** Caucasian**
** A brash and demanding customer who gives the lead protagonist a hard time at the convenience store. Though it‚Äôs a brief role (approximately 1 page), the character‚Äôs rude and dismissive attitude adds tension and realism to the scene.**

**Rude Male Customer**
** *****Age:***** 40‚Äì55**
** *****Ethnicity:***** Caucasian**
** A short but impactful role (around 1 page) portraying a difficult and unpleasant customer who clashes with the lead protagonist at the convenience store. The character‚Äôs curt and entitled demeanor highlights the everyday challenges faced by the protagonist.**

**Homeless Men (2 Roles)**

**‚Ä¢ Age: 30‚Äì50**

**‚Ä¢ Ethnicity: Open**

**Two male characters who appear briefly, portraying individuals experiencing homelessness. Small roles that bring depth and authenticity to the film‚Äôs setting.**

**Please submit headshots, a media reel, and any additional footage showcasing your dramatic range to - expressentryfilm@gmail.com**

**Shortlisted candidates will be called to make a self tape of their audition, they will be given a scene in advance to perform for the audition. Last date of submission is November 8th 2025.**

**Shoot dates: 29th & 30th Nov 2025**

**Additional: This is a passion project and a no budget film hence looking for volunteer actors who are highly passionate about their craft and will be able to commit to the project . This project is also a good opportunity for someone who is looking to build a portfolio as an actor.**

Casting call!

We're so excited to be casting for our female-focused feature film, Before Us!

Log line: Five strangers wrestle with motherhood and identity while, unbeknownst to them, their great grandmothers meddle from the afterlife. As their stories increasingly intertwine, the women must discover purpose from within themselves and from one another.

Genre: Dramedy

Paid, non-union

This first casting call includes our leads and key supporting roles, each paying $500-$750 depending on the success of fundraising and the final shooting schedule. We plan to shoot a teaser trailer and some social media content for fundraising purposes in November, with principal photography in January-February 2026. You can see full character breakdowns and audition submission instructions here: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1mi16s2oN0Gdn0KYzpTw6VKL1LIG1mytkHOXYFYM_a3M/edit?pli=1

We're casting for:

Izzy: 30, female, Chamorro (While a Chamorro actress is ideal, Izzy can be played by any Pacific Islander)

Agnes: 51, female, Chinese-American (While a Chinese actress is ideal, Agnes can be played by any actor of East Asian descent)

Sasha: 36, female, Black

Beatrice: Any age 50 or older, female, Black

Leticia: Any age 50 or older, female, Latina

Mabel: Any age 50 or older, female, Chinese (While a Chinese actress is ideal, she can be played by any actor of East Asian descent)

Man√•mko‚Äô: Any age 50 or older, female, Chamorro (While a Chamorro actress is ideal, she can be played by any Pacific Islander)

Margaret: Any age 50 or older, female, white

Foster: 29, male, any ethnicity

Please submit your audition via the form linked above by 11:59 pm on Saturday, November 1.

items.text:
¬∑ Title: This Side of Midnight

¬∑ Genre: Horror

¬∑ Logline: An eighteen-year-old girl must confront her inner demons, both real and metaphorical, as they test her to see if she is worthy of life itself after a brush with death.

¬∑ Role: Lilith ‚Äî Female, late teens to early 20s

A newly eighteen-year-old struggling with severe depression and suicidal thoughts. Intelligent, introspective, and haunted by her inner world. The emotional core of the story.

Note: Lead role. Must be comfortable portraying intense emotional states.

Zera ‚Äî Female, late teens to early 20s

Lilith‚Äôs best friend. Empathetic and determined, trying desperately to remind Lilith that she matters.

Dad ‚Äî Male, 40s‚Äì50s (flexible)

A concerned father trying to reconnect with his daughter after finding her following a suicide attempt. Must convey deep emotion with subtlety.

Mom ‚Äî Female, 40s‚Äì50s (flexible)

 A mother struggling to cope as her daughter begins to withdraw, stop eating, and lose hope.

Sibling ‚Äî Any gender (preferably male), 10‚Äì15 (flexible)

Appears in one scene. No speaking lines, but must express strong emotion through facial expression and presence.

Cashier ‚Äî Any gender/age

Background role, no speaking lines.

¬∑ Production Company: Cassidy Cheldelin ‚Äî Writer, Director, Videographer, Editor
Jess Lange ‚Äî Co-Director, Casting Director, Producer

¬∑ Production Type: Student Film

¬∑ Contact Information: Contact: Jess Lange ‚Äî escapemindproductions@gmail.com
Instagram: @escapemind.productions 

¬∑ Run Time: Short (16 minutes)

¬∑ Compensation: Unpaid

¬∑ Union Status: Non-Union

¬∑ Audition Information: 

Format: Digital Submission

Please record a 1‚Äì2 minute monologue of your choice (preferably horror or drama) that demonstrates emotional depth. Include your name, age, preferred email & phone number, and desired role in the email. Name, age, and role for slate. 

Lilith Auditions: Monologue may be up to 5 minutes or the attached scene from the screenplay.

Dad Auditions: May choose to perform from the attached scene.

Submit to: escapemindproductions@gmail.com
Deadline: November 5, 11:59 PM (MST)

¬∑ Shooting Schedule: Mid-November (before Thanksgiving) table read, 11/8/25 at 12 (MST), location upon casting

¬∑ Filming Location: Black Forest, CO, 80908 & Colorado Springs, CO, North Academy Blvd.

¬∑ Project Description:

Two filmmakers are passionate about exploring mental health through the lens of horror. While this is not a professional production, we approach the project with deep respect and dedication to the craft. This Side of Midnight follows Lilith as she confronts her literal demons and manifestations of her struggles with mental illness, who test her will to live. When she ultimately fails, she is tragically taken, symbolizing the devastating reality of losing the battle against one‚Äôs own mind.

Lilith and Dad Scene 

Int. BEDROOM - MORNING

The screen flickers to her dad, shaking her awake

Dad

Lilith! Wake up! Please- Please, breathe please.

Lilith sits up suddenly, her breathing is chaotic, and she is in fear.

Her dad sighs in relief

Dad

Oh, thank god you are ok. I was about to call 911. What happened??

LILITH (studdering)

I- I don't know

She looks around the room, noticing the empty pill bottle next to her pillow, and she erratically shoves it further underneath so as not to let her dad see.

LILITH

Must've just been too much melatonin..

Dad

You scared the crap out of me and you're mother. Zera too.

Lilith looks defeated as her father sits more formally on her bed.

Dad

That reminds me, you should probably call her. She was worried sick about you.

LILITH

I will- I will do that.

Dad (in relief)

Good. You missed the bus. I have to go to work n' can't drive you- so have the day off.

LiLITH (under her breath)

T-Thanks.

DAD

A mental Health day- y'know? You deserve it.

Lilith's expression doesn't change. Her dad stands up and begins to put on his jacket

DAD

Let me know if you need anything, okay?

FOR VALID EUROPEAN PASSPORT HOLDERS ONLY !!!

We are a professional dance company and we are looking for professional dancers to work with us (dance show) during summer season 2026 ( from March-November) at 5 star hotels in Crete , Greece .

We provide accommodation , insurance and contract.

If you want to have the opportunity to be part of our professional team and live  under the Cretan sun , then this your chance. 

Send us your CV at pastoumarilena@yahoo.com , so we can arrange your interview and give you more information. 

Messages sent at messenger won‚Äôt be answered. Only e-mails , please.

Best Regards,

Marilena.

[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1nk_znzhtPMbimUu4qTBmFBJyqiFuuUusmZblwOXPCnc/edit?usp=drive_link](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1nk_znzhtPMbimUu4qTBmFBJyqiFuuUusmZblwOXPCnc/edit?usp=drive_link)

CASTING
TOUGH CHARACTERS

The Kharmel Cochrane casting team are seeking big and tall characters with football skills and threatening energy to play the opposition in a major sportswear commercial.

20s - 30s, all genders, ‚Äúintimidating ‚Äî physically and in attitude‚Äù

Filming: Mid Nov - Mid Dec (Barcelona)
No previous acting experience required. Paid opportunity.
Talent must live in the UK.

To apply, email streetcasting@kharmelcochrane.co.uk
with the subject ‚ÄúTough Footballer‚Äù.

Please include full name, age, location, selfie, intro and any footballing experience.

Kharmel Cochrane Casting

SYNOPSIS: When granddaughter, Red, stops receiving letters from her sick grandmother she insists on visiting. Surprised, she finds a man who claims to be her grandmother‚Äôs new carer. As he continues to ask strange questions and refuses to let Red see her, she realises the man is taking advantage of her poor grandmother, using medicines to make her sicker. When confronted the man becomes enraged and is forced to kill little Red. 

Wanted: 2 actors (1 x M, 1 x F) for exciting new short film ‚ÄòIn His Care‚Äô. Shooting in Hertfordshire, w/c 24th November, student project from an award-winning Film & TV course.

- RED (Female, 24 ‚Äì 30)

- Description: Mid to late 20s

Red is a simple, reserved girl. She is kind and holds herself highly. But when it comes to her grandma, she is extremely protective, fierce even. She is perceptive and head strong and will do anything to find what‚Äôs happening at grandma‚Äôs house.

- Height: 5‚Äô5 ‚Äì 5‚Äô9

- Appearance: Red is a modest girl. She dresses simple when visiting her grandmother, always wearing the infamous red scarf that her grandmother gave her.

- Pay Category: travel expenses and food covered

- HARRY (Male, 35 - 50)

- Description: Mid 30s to 50

Harry is carer to Ruth, conniving and manipulative; calculated and dominating. He knows what he wants and how to get it. He isn‚Äôt a smart perpetrator but rather simple-minded praying on those who can‚Äôt defend themselves and has no one to defend them. He has been getting away with it until a young girl with a fiery soul starts to uncover his secret.

Height: Tall (6ft approx.)

- Appearance: Harry is a seemingly ordinary guy on the outside. Charismatic, confident, tall, handsome, well kept. If you walked past him down the street, he may smile or wink at you. He uses his looks and caring fa√ßade as leverage.

- Pay category: travel expenses and food covered

If you‚Äôre interested, please submit showreels and any enquiries to sheldonkieran4@gmail.com by 7th November

items.text:
Hello fellow NYC actors and filmmakers! 

My name is Eunji, an actor, filmmaker and founder of Dreama. My company is opening a new workshop for actors, DREAMA ACTING LAB üíú

This is going to be very special and transformative experience as an actors and artists to develop your acting skills to another and deeper level.

The registration is now OPEN and you can submit this google form below:
https://forms.gle/ofW1Yu2MhihCvfV68

Can't wait to see you beautiful & talented actors in the same room together for this new journey! 

Hugs,

Eunji Lim

ü™ª[DREAMA ACTING LAB] in Fall - Winter 2025üî¨

Hello dear DREAMA Family & Friends üòá
Dreama is proudly opening a new acting workshop!

üìçAbout DREAMA ACTING LAB
Dreama Acting Lab is opened for Actors and people who want to learn acting from Method Acting to Dreama Method created by Eunji Lim, our artistic director.
For actors, you will develop the ability to tap into your deeper self, train your awareness, imagination and creativity by learning about your instrument with sensitivity and vulnerability. Through our abundant techniques, you will amplify your stage presence and discover how to co-exist with others through breath, while refining your body, mind, and soul to craft yourself in order to meet your character at the ‚Äúintersection.‚Äù

ü™ÑHOW TO REGISTER
Submit Google Form (Link below)
üîóhttps://forms.gle/ofW1Yu2MhihCvfV68

ü™Ñ REGISTRATION DUE DATE
Until November 5th (Wed)

ü™Ñ SCHEDULE
November 10th ‚Äî December 29th
Mondays, 6 pm - 9 pm

ü™Ñ LOCATION:
Studio in Manhattan
(TBA for Registered Students)

ü™Ñ For Whom:
- Actors who hope to develop their acting techniques and create their own method
- Actors who want to take their craft to the next level
- Actors who want to refine their awareness and imagination to be fully present on stage
- Actors who want to fully embody their character and connect deeply with co-actors on stage
- Actors who love learning and exploring Method acting

üìßINQUIRY
dreamaworkshop@gmail.com

We will look forward to meeting new actors and artists for our new journey together! üö¢‚ù§Ô∏è

Hope you shine as you always do ‚úãüèª‚ú®ü§öüèª

Let‚Äôs Dreama!

We‚Äôre currently casting for **two main characters** in our upcoming **third-year short film project**, a **horror-comedy** shooting in **Coventry** (with the possibility of additional locations ‚Äî confirmed actors will be informed in advance).

üìÖ **Filming Period:** Mid-February to March 2026
üéûÔ∏è **Length:** Approx. 15 minutes
üé≠ **Genre:** Horror Comedy

This is an **unpaid student production**, but we will **cover travel costs and catering** during filming days.

We‚Äôre looking for **dedicated and enthusiastic actors** who are passionate about working on creative projects and open to collaborating with a student film crew.

If you‚Äôre interested, please email **davist11@coventry.ac.uk** with your **headshot, showreel (if available), and a short bio**.
Once you get in touch, I‚Äôll send over **all the details about the audition process** and what to expect.

We‚Äôre aiming to **lock in our final cast by January**, so please make sure you‚Äôre available for the filming period mentioned above.

This is a great opportunity to gain on-set experience, expand your portfolio, and be part of a fun and ambitious student film! üé•‚ú®
